        <remark>
          <p>
            The cross product of two vectors <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m> is completely determined geometrically by the following three properties:
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <m>\vu \times \vv</m> is orthogonal to both <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m>.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Between the two possible orthogonal directions, the direction <m>\vu \times \vv</m> is determined by the right-hand rule.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  The magnitude of <m>\vu \times \vv</m> is equal to the area of the parallelogram formed by the two vectors.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
            
          </p>
        </remark>

